description:
The Great British Sewing Bee - Series 4

Amateur sewers take on challenges as they compete to be named Britain's best home sewer.

BBC (2016) - 8 Episodes
 
http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07c9w27
_______________________________________

832x468 resolution - MP4 files

Video Codec h.264
Audio Codec AAC

With subtitles - enjoy !!
_______________________________________

    Basic Construction
    Ten sewers follow a difficult pattern for a woman's top made up of four pieces.

    Children's Week
    The sewers hope to show the judges that they can make beautiful clothes on a small scale.

    Lingerie Week
    The sewers work with the fiddliest of pattern pieces and the most delicate fabric.

    International Week
    The sewers must tackle techniques and garment styles from other cultures and continents.

    1960s Week
    The sewing room is transported back to the 1960s.

    Activewear
    In the quarter-final, the five remaining sewers sweat it out over activewear.

    Puzzling Patterns and Pattern Cutting
    In the semi-final, the sewers are tasked with making an asymmetric yoked skirt.

    Evening Wear
    The three finalists create three pieces of evening wear to try to impress the judges
